 <stuff category="711">
  <name>Bix Plasma Player</name>
  <providerid>api.kde-look.org</providerid>
  <author>zayronXIO</author>
  <homepage>https://store.kde.org/p/2199942</homepage>
  <licence></licence>
  <version>alfa 0.2.1</version>
  <rating>58</rating>
  <downloads>20280</downloads>
  <installedfile>/home/laghab/.local/share/plasma/plasmoids/Bix.Plasma.Player/</installedfile>
  <id>2199942</id>
  <releasedate>2025-10-29</releasedate>
  <summary>&lt;p>Bix Plasma is a music player in development. This is the alpha version, still with many tasks ahead.&lt;br />Currently it only supports mp3 but will soon support a greater number of formats.&lt;br />&lt;br />The plasmoid aims to provide an experience similar to a standalone music player, but keep in mind that it is not one. It is implemented on Plasma, and as a result, a failure in Bix affects Plasma and vice versa.&lt;br />&lt;br />It currently loads your local music collection correctly from the folder you choose in the settings. It loads the metadata of your audio tracks and includes fully functional buttons (prev, play, next, favorites, shuffle mode).&lt;br />&lt;br />&lt;b>Known missing features:&lt;/b>&lt;br />&lt;/p>&lt;ul>&lt;li>Option to add your own playlists&lt;br />&lt;/li>&lt;li>Artists tab&lt;br />&lt;/li>&lt;li>System to detect apps that obstruct the plasmoid's view&lt;br />&lt;/li>&lt;li>Support for formats other than MP3&lt;br />&lt;/li>&lt;/ul>&lt;br />&lt;br />&lt;b>Donate me&lt;/b>&lt;br />&lt;b>If you like my job and you want to help me, invite me to a cafe. Here is a link so you can donate through PayPal if you wish:&lt;/b>&lt;br />&lt;a href="https://www.paypal.me/zayronxio">&lt;b>Donate&lt;/b>&lt;/a></summary>
  <changelog></changelog>
  <preview>https://images.pling.com/cache/770x540-4/img/00/00/24/01/13/2199942/bix.png</preview>
  <previewBig>https://images.pling.com/cache/770x540-4/img/00/00/24/01/13/2199942/bix.png</previewBig>
